# Performance & Efficiency

## Big O Analysis

- Prefer O(1) or O(log n) algorithms. Justify any O(n²) or worse.
- Comment the time/space complexity on non-trivial algorithms.

## N+1 Query Prevention

Queries inside loops are **forbidden**. Use JOINs, subqueries, or batching.

```typescript
// ❌ BAD — N+1: one query per unit
const units = await db.select().from(units);
for (const unit of units) {
  const tenant = await db.select().from(tenants).where(eq(tenants.id, unit.tenantId));
}

// ✅ GOOD — single query with JOIN
const result = await db
  .select()
  .from(units)
  .leftJoin(tenants, eq(units.tenantId, tenants.id));
```

## Memory & Streams

- Use Streams (Node.js `Readable`/`Transform`) for heavy reports (occupancy, financial, CSV/PDF export).
- Paginate all list endpoints. Default page size ≤ 50.
- Avoid loading entire collections into memory.

## Database

- Add indexes for columns used in WHERE, JOIN, and ORDER BY.
- Use database transactions for operations that modify multiple tables.
- Prefer `EXISTS` over `COUNT(*)` for existence checks.
